The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, August 02, 2004 				 Orchid puts issue on hold
																								Chennai, Aug. 1 (PTI): Orchid Chemicals and Pharmaceuticals has decided to hold back its $75 million foreign currency convertible bonds (FCCB) due to hardening of interest rates in the US.																								We have not shelved the bonds issue. We are waiting for the rates to improve, managing director K. Raghavendra Rao said.																								The company received the shareholders approval for the FCCB issue on April 10. 																								The issue is aimed at funding the companys long-term growth plans. 
